<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,512,755]" box="[151,558,512,539]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,512,539]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,512,755]" box="[199,1335,548,575]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,548,575]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe; also North Africa. 
<collectingCountry box="[663,762,549,575]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: three northern provinces and Algarve in the south.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,512,755]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,585,611]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ecology.</emphasis>
Most of the capture locations of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[846,941,585,611]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
were situated along open water (waterfalls, marshlands, riverbanks). In northwestern Europe, the species is generally considered as part of the hygropetric fauna (
<bibRefCitation author="Pollet, M." box="[228,363,657,683]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref34362" refString="Pollet, M. (2000) A documented Red List of the dolichopodid flies (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) of Flanders [in Dutch with English summary]. Communications of the Institute of Nature Conservation, 8, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2000">Pollet 2000</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[412,494,657,683]" name="Croatia" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Croatia</collectingCountry>
it is found to prefer riverbeds to springs (
<bibRefCitation author="Pollet, M. &amp; Ivkovic, M." box="[960,1216,657,683]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="401 - 428" refId="ref35148" refString="Pollet, M. &amp; Ivkovic, M. (2018) Dolichopodidae of riverbeds and springs in Croatia with an updated checklist of Croatia (Diptera). Zootaxa, 4455 (3), 401 - 428. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4455.3.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Pollet &amp; Ivković 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,512,755]" box="[199,456,692,719]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,692,719]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
4.6 (rare).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,512,755]" box="[199,641,728,755]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,728,755]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Activity period.</emphasis>
May, July, September.
</paragraph>
